The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning algorithms to optimize a global utility function, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The concept of collective intelligence is also a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the application of these algorithms to internet traffic routing falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
